ans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Burchill was born about 1155, in Crickhowell, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Richard Burghill, was 37 and his mother, Anne Pitcher, was 37. He had at least 3 sons with Jane de Walbieffe."},"et":{"Abt 1155–":"umbes 1155–Surnud","1155–Male":"1155–Surnud","1157–Female":"1157–Surnud","1177–Male":"1177–Surnud","1197–Male":"1197–Surnud","1202–1272":"1202–1272","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1120–Female":"1120–Surnud","1202":"1202","1157":"1157","Abt 1155":"umbes 1155","1177":"1177","1155":"1155","1120":"1120","1197":"1197","1272":"1272","abt 1177":"umbes 1177","about 1197":"umbes 1197","Llanfair,Cilgedin,Monmouthshire,Wales":"Llanfair Grange, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Crickhowell, Cantref Selyf, Wales":"Crickhowell, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1155–":"noin 1155–Kuollut","1155–Male":"1155–Kuollut","1157–Female":"1157–Kuollut","1177–Male":"1177–Kuollut","1197–Male":"1197–Kuollut","1202–1272":"1202–1272","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1120–Female":"1120–Kuollut","1202":"1202","1157":"1157","Abt 1155":"noin 1155","1177":"1177","1155":"1155","1120":"1120","1197":"1197","1272":"1272","abt 1177":"noin 1177","about 1197":"noin 1197","Llanfair,Cilgedin,Monmouthshire,Wales":"Llanfair Grange, Monmouthshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Crickhowell, Cantref Selyf, Wales":"Crickhowell, Breconshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Br